#!/bin/sh
# CDC-ECM USB gadget: present a USB network device to the host (your Mac) so you can SSH in over the
# USB-C cable — no serial, no HDMI. Plug the Radxa's OTG/power USB-C port into the Mac.
#   Mac side: set the new USB network interface to 10.66.0.2/24, then:  ssh root@10.66.0.1  (pw: artlynk)
GADGET_IP=10.66.0.1
GADGET_MASK=255.255.255.0

case "$1" in
  start)
	UDC=$(ls /sys/class/udc/ 2>/dev/null | head -n1)
	if [ -z "$UDC" ]; then
		echo "usbgadget: no UDC found (USB port not in peripheral/otg mode?) — skipping"
		exit 0
	fi
	mount -t configfs none /sys/kernel/config 2>/dev/null
	G=/sys/kernel/config/usb_gadget/g1
	mkdir -p "$G/strings/0x409" "$G/configs/c.1/strings/0x409" "$G/functions/ecm.usb0"
	echo 0x1d6b > "$G/idVendor"
	echo 0x0104 > "$G/idProduct"
	echo 0x0200 > "$G/bcdUSB"
	echo "ArtLynk"        > "$G/strings/0x409/manufacturer"
	echo "ArtLynk Bridge" > "$G/strings/0x409/product"
	echo "artlynk0001"    > "$G/strings/0x409/serialnumber"
	echo "ECM" > "$G/configs/c.1/strings/0x409/configuration"
	echo 250   > "$G/configs/c.1/MaxPower"
	echo "02:00:00:66:00:01" > "$G/functions/ecm.usb0/dev_addr"
	echo "02:00:00:66:00:02" > "$G/functions/ecm.usb0/host_addr"
	ln -sf "$G/functions/ecm.usb0" "$G/configs/c.1/"
	echo "$UDC" > "$G/UDC" && echo "usbgadget: bound ECM gadget to UDC $UDC"
	# assign the device-side interface (the ECM gadget creates a usb* netdev)
	IF=""
	for i in 1 2 3 4 5; do
		for n in /sys/class/net/usb*; do [ -e "$n" ] && IF=$(basename "$n") && break; done
		[ -n "$IF" ] && break
		sleep 1
	done
	if [ -n "$IF" ]; then
		ifconfig "$IF" "$GADGET_IP" netmask "$GADGET_MASK" up
		echo "usbgadget: $IF = $GADGET_IP   (ssh root@$GADGET_IP)"
	else
		echo "usbgadget: gadget bound but no usb* netdev appeared yet"
	fi
	;;
  stop)
	echo "" > /sys/kernel/config/usb_gadget/g1/UDC 2>/dev/null
	;;
  *) echo "Usage: $0 {start|stop}"; exit 1;;
esac
